article:
'Beta globin' ('HBB', 'Î²-globin' or 'haemoglobin, beta' or preferably
'haemoglobin subunit beta') is a globin protein, which along with alpha globin
(HBA), makes up the most common form of hemoglobin in adult humans, the HbA. It is 146 amino acids long and has a molecular weight of
15,867 Da. Normal adult human HbA is a heterotetramer consisting of two alpha
chains and two beta chains.
